Mpumalanga police have arrested two suspects after they allegedly stole an ATM. According to the cops, the pair and three other suspects held staff at gunpoint at a filling station near Secunda on Friday. Police spokesperson Colonel Donald Mdhluli said the fives suspects that were heavily armed arrived at the filling station at around 02:00. Some of them were wearing police bulletproof vests. "The suspects, who were armed with rifles, tied employees and detached the ATM, loaded it on a trailer and towed it away. "The incident was reported to police who swiftly responded and activated their resources in search of the suspects." Police later spotted a BMW X3 matching the description of the wanted vehicle. "A high-speed chase ensued until the BMW was brought to a halt near Morgenzon. Inside the vehicle, police found number plates and tools to remove the ATM. "The suspects were arrested, and the vehicle confiscated. The car will form part of the investigation. The two men are expected to appear in court on Monday." Mdhluli said they were looking for the remaining suspects.